  <wpt lat="41.228" lon="-96.1205">
    <time>2026-04-25T14:00:00</time>
    <name>GCBM5P9</name>
    <desc>Maker Magic: It's Not Trash, It's a Geocache! 🪄🎩 by J&amp;LA, Event Cache (1.0/1.0)</desc>
    <url>https://coord.info/GCBM5P9</url>
    <urlname>Maker Magic: It's Not Trash, It's a Geocache! 🪄🎩</urlname>
    <sym>Geocache</sym>
    <type>Geocache|Event Cache</type>
    <groundspeak:cache id="10348927" archived="False" available="True" xmlns:groundspeak="http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1">
      <groundspeak:name>Maker Magic: It's Not Trash, It's a Geocache! 🪄🎩</groundspeak:name>
      <groundspeak:placed_by>J&amp;LA</groundspeak:placed_by>
      <groundspeak:owner id="2758194">J&amp;LA</groundspeak:owner>
      <groundspeak:type>Event Cache</groundspeak:type>
      <groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container>
      <groundspeak:attributes>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="26" inc="1">Public transportation nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
      </groundspeak:attributes>
      <groundspeak:difficulty>1.0</groundspeak:difficulty>
      <groundspeak:terrain>1.0</groundspeak:terrain>
      <groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country>
      <groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state>
      <groundspeak:short_description html="True">&lt;b&gt;25 April 2026, 14:00 - 16:00&lt;/b&gt;</groundspeak:short_description>
      <groundspeak:long_description html="True">&lt;h2 style="font-style:italic;text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://img.geocaching.com:443/de3e117e-f057-4cb5-9704-1be1ee53db47.png" width="65%" /&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

If you attend this event, you will earn a special souvenir! See below note from the geocaching.com blog for more info. 

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;The title of this cache is a small nod to the popular GIFF 2022 film of the same title  We now sometimes jokingly chant, &amp;quot;It&amp;#39;s not trash, it&amp;#39;s a GEOCACHE&amp;quot; as we rifle through our stash trying to decide if an item is worthy of a new life as a geocache or not. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
We&amp;#39;ll be exploring ideas on how to make a creative cache, including turning unwanted &amp;amp;/or broken items into new hides (aka recycling), &amp;amp; may include comversations about themes, locations, logistics, cache page write ups &amp;amp; other important aspects of cache-building. If there&amp;#39;s a possibility you might come, please log a will-attend in case we need to bring extra supplies along to accomodate. We probably won't be actually building any containers or holders today, but we will definitely attempt to bring some oddball items to ponder over. You are also welcome to bring your own ideas along!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;Saturday April 25, 2026&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;2-4pm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;Millard Public Library&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;13214 Westwood Ln&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:16px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"&gt;Meeting Room 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;center&gt;&lt;a href="www.facebook.com/groups/Nebraskache"&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/3ab1f796-0f20-4aeb-8dfe-f9dbcbfa7236_l.jpg" style="width:260px;height:130px;" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/center&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
"&lt;font color="green"&gt;Maker Magic is back!&lt;/font&gt;
The joy of finally finding a well-hidden container. The surprise and delight at encountering a clever gadget cache. The twinkle in a cacher’s eye when signing a logbook. It’s all magic.

We’re bringing back that magical feeling with Maker Magic, a moment of celebration and inspiration for creative cache hides.Between April 9 and 30, 2026, the geocaching community is invited to host and attend Maker Magic events to earn a special souvenir."
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; </groundspeak:long_description>
