  <wpt lat="41.265233" lon="-96.039317">
    <time>2026-03-14T08:00:00</time>
    <name>GCBJNMY</name>
    <desc>March Geo Breakfast by Monty12, Event Cache (1.0/1.0)</desc>
    <url>https://coord.info/GCBJNMY</url>
    <urlname>March Geo Breakfast</urlname>
    <sym>Geocache</sym>
    <type>Geocache|Event Cache</type>
    <groundspeak:cache id="10304679" archived="False" available="True" xmlns:groundspeak="http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1">
      <groundspeak:name>March Geo Breakfast</groundspeak:name>
      <groundspeak:placed_by>Monty12</groundspeak:placed_by>
      <groundspeak:owner id="1253738">Monty12</groundspeak:owner>
      <groundspeak:type>Event Cache</groundspeak:type>
      <groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container>
      <groundspeak:attributes>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="1">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
      </groundspeak:attributes>
      <groundspeak:difficulty>1.0</groundspeak:difficulty>
      <groundspeak:terrain>1.0</groundspeak:terrain>
      <groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country>
      <groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state>
      <groundspeak:short_description html="True">&lt;b&gt;14 March 2026, 08:00 - 09:30&lt;/b&gt;</groundspeak:short_description>
      <groundspeak:long_description html="True">&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:18px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;March 14th 0800-0930&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;Please join your fellow cachers for the monthly Deli Caching Breakfast.  This is a monthly event so you all know where to go.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;The deli is wheelchair accessible and offers three options:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;1.  a full breakfast and lunch menu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;2.  purchase something (like a donut or yogurt) from the store and enjoy it at the event&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:20px;"&gt;3.  just join us for the fun.  No purchase is necessary to attend this event.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description>
      <groundspeak:encoded_hints>
      </groundspeak:encoded_hints>
      <groundspeak:logs>
        <groundspeak:log id="1349045021">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-03-14T19:02:35Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="4345423">yhtak57</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Thanks for hosting</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1348984335">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-03-14T19:00:00Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="1033306">Shadow Chasers</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Lively breakfast this morning!  Yay Pi!</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1350503347">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-03-14T19:00:00Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="20507951">CRVonFange</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Find #6488 (Event #81) 

I haven't had many opportunities for caching this winter, but with a series of Pi Day Souvenirs available this weekend I took a look at the geocaching map to see where I could have the best opportunity for earning the souvenirs and I noticed that I still had not completed the ghost geoart that was hidden earlier this fall. Since I had all of the puzzles solved and coordinates updated, I thought that even if I only found a portion of the ghost between attending two geocaching events it would be worth making the trip to Omaha. I suggested to my muggle mother that we take advantage of the nice weather ahead of the next winter snow storm and make a quick trip south to celebrate my cousin’s birthday this weekend rather than waiting until next weekend (her actual birthday is Wednesday). 

In addition to moving one step closer to having attended 100 geocaching events, which I will reach later today if Community Celebration Events and Cache In Trash Out Events are included, I enjoy getting to hear everyone's caching adventures or misadventures. I wish that there were more events closer to where I live, so I didn’t have to always spend time driving rather than caching, but I haven’t quite worked up the courage to start hosting any in my hometown although I certainly have thought about it and may hold my first in conjunction with a new series of caches that I am hiding. In addition to winning a mini Cherry Pie as a door prize, I was able to connect with Brian/Bryan of bhjalarson and his son Jacob, who now caches as PowerRanger13, who were also heading to some of the ghost caches this morning so I didn’t have to cache by myself.  

As I picked up my backpack to leave, I realized that I forgot to share the trackables that have been traveling with me with the group for discovery. If you attended and are interested in discovering them, please reach out to me via the geocaching message center.
</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1349030233">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-03-14T18:20:24Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="4119598">Mizz Piggy</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Attended with Bill my bear!  Great breakfast, (French toast this time), and of course enjoyable time with some of our favorite people.  Thanks Becky for hosting…..and the PIE DAY fun.</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1348985879">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-03-14T16:32:35Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="15311687">MzunguDeb</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Enjoyed Breakfast with the group. Thanks for the pie.</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
      </groundspeak:logs>
    </groundspeak:cache>
  </wpt>
  <wpt lat="40.733267" lon="-96.599517">
